In Genesis 16, Abram came to one of these periods in his life. After the early years of following the Lord, moving to Canaan, making wise choices, resisting temptation, and leading in worship, he had now settled in and time was passing. He struggled to believe God in this rough periodâ€“a dry period lacking adventures of faith. As we will see, he failed badly at a critical point in trying to assess the will of God.